OL,3,CCare home shut down after inspections
OL,4,Cfound it 'unsafe and understaffed'
OL,6,FThe CQC first inspected Blossoms Care
OL,7,FHome in January and moved to cancel
OL,8,Fthe home's registration - effectively
OL,9,Fclosing it in the process.
OL,11,FThe company appealed the decision but
OL,12,Fa second inspection in November - when
OL,13,Fit was caring for 15 people - found
OL,14,Feven more issues with its services,
OL,15,Fincluding not knowing that three of
OL,16,Fits residents had epilepsy.
OL,18,FBlossoms Care Home Limited then
OL,19,Fwithdrew its appeal and stopped
OL,20,Foperating.
